<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE1FE6F48F75015FD6BF869" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418FE1FE6F48F75015FD6BF869" blockId="431.[151,1436,1777,2017]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE1FE6F48F75015FEE4F8A2" bold="true" box="[199,321,1849,1874]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE1FE6F49795015FE27F8A1" box="[329,386,1849,1873]" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE1FE6F49A45015FD96F8A1" box="[404,563,1849,1873]" captionStart="PLATE 137" captionStartId="432.[151,233,1981,2004]" captionTargetBox="[356,1229,203,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-41@432.[347,1240,175,1960]" captionTargetPageId="432" captionText="PLATE 137. Ponomarenkoa ellenbergeri sp. nov. A. Holotype. Length 2.7 mm. B. Paratype. Length 2.8 mm. C. Head in ventral view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278854/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plate 137A–C</figureCitation>
): fully winged; occipital carina complete; antennae 10-segmented; fore wing with three cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal, median and submedian), with metacarpus shorter than pterostigma;; tibial spurs 1/2/2. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE1FE6F49CC50ADFDF5F869" box="[508,592,1921,1945]" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE1FE6F48F75089FCC2F84D" box="[199,871,1957,1982]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="007606418FE1FE6F48F75089FCC2F84D" blockId="431.[151,1436,1777,2017]" box="[199,871,1957,1982]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE1FE6F48F75089FEC5F84E" bold="true" box="[199,352,1957,1982]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from Baltic and Burmese amber.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE1FE7148F750E5FC10FF5F" lastPageId="433" lastPageNumber="434" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="007606418FE1FE6F48F750E5FE2BF811" blockId="431.[151,1436,1777,2017]" box="[199,398,1993,2017]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE1FE6F48F750E5FEB4F811" bold="true" box="[199,273,1993,2017]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Hosts.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="54B656C98FFEFE7048A75091FE25F801" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278854" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5278854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278854/files/figure.png" pageId="432" pageNumber="433" startId="432.[151,233,1981,2004]" targetBox="[356,1229,203,1934]" targetPageId="432">
<paragraph id="007606418FFEFE7048A75091FE25F801" blockId="432.[151,1436,1981,2033]" pageId="432" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFEFE7048A75091FEBAF824" bold="true" box="[151,287,1981,2004]" pageId="432" pageNumber="433">PLATE 137.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFEFE7049185091FDE3F823" authority="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He, 2013" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" box="[296,582,1981,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Ponomarenkoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="432" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ellenbergeri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFEFE7049185091FDE3F823" box="[296,582,1981,2003]" italics="true" pageId="432" pageNumber="433">Ponomarenkoa ellenbergeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFEFE704A7F5092FD60F824" bold="true" box="[591,709,1981,2004]" pageId="432" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="298E67288FFEFE704A7F5092FD06F823" box="[591,675,1982,2003]" pageId="432" pageNumber="433" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A.
</emphasis>
Holotype. Length 2.7 mm. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFEFE704BDD5092FBA1F823" bold="true" box="[1005,1028,1982,2003]" pageId="432" pageNumber="433">B.</emphasis>
Paratype. Length 2.8 mm. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFEFE704D175091FAE5F824" bold="true" box="[1319,1344,1981,2004]" pageId="432" pageNumber="433">C.</emphasis>
Head in ventral view, holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="007606418FFFFE7148F757B4FC10FF5F" blockId="433.[151,1436,151,572]" box="[199,949,151,176]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE7148F757B4FED1FF40" bold="true" box="[199,372,151,176]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">World species.</emphasis>
Two species are known, one in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38FFFFE714B3457BBFC14FF5F" box="[772,945,151,175]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FFFFE7148F75790FACBFDCB" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418FFFFE7148F75790FACBFDCB" blockId="433.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE7148F75790FE9EFF24" bold="true" box="[199,315,188,212]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08FFFFE7149725790FE6BFF24" author="Olmi" box="[322,462,188,212]" firstAuthor="Olmi" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" pagination="109 - 395" refId="ref365350" refString="Olmi, M. (1991 [&quot; 1989 &quot;]) Supplement to the revision of the world Dryinidae (Hymenoptera Chrysidoidea). Frustula entomologica, N. S., 12 (25), 109 - 395." type="journal article" year="1991">Olmi (1991)</bibRefCitation>
described the new subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714B115790FC06FF24" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1991" box="[801,931,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Laberitinae">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714B115790FC06FF24" box="[801,931,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberitinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714C2D5790FAD1FF24" authority="Ponomarenko, 1988" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[1053,1396,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714C2D5790FB22FF24" box="[1053,1159,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberites</emphasis>
Ponomarenko, 1988
</taxonomicName>
. At description time, this genus included two species, 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714AF957CCFBB8FF07" authority="Ponomarenko, 1988" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[713,1053,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polonicus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714AF957CCFC93FF08" box="[713,822,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">polonicus</emphasis>
Ponomarenko, 1988
</taxonomicName>
,(from Baltic amber) and 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714D0C57CCFA39FF07" box="[1340,1436,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">antiquus</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE7148AE5628FE9BFEEC" authority="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He, 2013" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" box="[158,318,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ponomarenko" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Ponomarenko</taxonomicName>
, 1981) (from Taimyr amber). 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714AA65628FC94FEEC" authority="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He, 2013" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" box="[662,817,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ponomarenko" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Ponomarenko</taxonomicName>
however did not want to describe really a new genus; for this reason, she did not designate a 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714A775604FD47FEB0" bold="true" box="[583,738,295,320]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FFFFE714A775604FD27FEB0" box="[583,642,296,320]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714AD8560BFC26FECF" authority="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He, 2013" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" box="[744,899,295,319]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ponomarenko" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Ponomarenko</taxonomicName>
in fact simply used a collective name to include the two above species considered of uncertain generic position. 
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08FFFFE714B545660FC4AFE94" author="Olmi" box="[868,1007,332,356]" firstAuthor="Olmi" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" pagination="109 - 395" refId="ref365350" refString="Olmi, M. (1991 [&quot; 1989 &quot;]) Supplement to the revision of the world Dryinidae (Hymenoptera Chrysidoidea). Frustula entomologica, N. S., 12 (25), 109 - 395." type="journal article" year="1991">Olmi (1991)</bibRefCitation>
did not understand that 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714CCF5660FACCFE94" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[1279,1385,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714CCF5660FACCFE94" box="[1279,1385,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a collective name and not a true genus, so that, after separation of 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714B9A565CFBAFFE77" box="[938,1034,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">antiquus</emphasis>
, considered belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714D0B565CFA30FE77" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[1339,1429,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Dryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714D0B565CFA30FE77" box="[1339,1429,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Dryinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, designated 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE71492556B8FE27FE5C" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[277,386,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polonicus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE71492556B8FE27FE5C" box="[277,386,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">polonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FFFFE71499856B8FE7DFE5C" box="[424,472,404,428]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">type</typeStatus>
species and described a new subfamily (
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714B9256B8FB80FE5C" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1991" box="[930,1061,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Laberitinae">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714B9256B8FB80FE5C" box="[930,1061,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberitinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) based on 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714CAF56B8FAACFE5C" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[1183,1289,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714CAF56B8FAACFE5C" box="[1183,1289,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Afterwards, however, 
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08FFFFE714938569BFDB6FE3F" author="Olmi &amp; Bechly" box="[264,531,439,463]" firstAuthor="Olmi" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref367353" refString="Olmi, M. &amp; Bechly, G. (2001) New parasitic wasps from Baltic amber (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Dryinidae). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie B, Nr. 306, 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="2001">Olmi &amp; Bechly (2001)</bibRefCitation>
considered unvalid 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714B325694FCC9FE20" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[770,876,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714B325694FCC9FE20" box="[770,876,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714BEB569BFBD3FE3F" authority="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He, 2013" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" box="[987,1142,439,463]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ponomarenko" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Ponomarenko</taxonomicName>
did not designate a 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FFFFE714D5C5694FA39FE20" box="[1388,1436,440,464]" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">type</typeStatus>
species (Art. 13.3 of ICZN 1999). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714A9956F0FCB6FE04" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[681,787,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714A9956F0FCB6FE04" box="[681,787,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unvalid, because it is only a collective name including fossils (Art. 20 of ICZN 1999). Because of the unavailability of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714BA7552CFBA4FDE8" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[919,1025,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Laberites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714BA7552CFBA4FDE8" box="[919,1025,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Laberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a new name, 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714C84552CFAFBFDE8" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="2010" box="[1204,1374,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Ponomarenkoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714C84552CFAFBFDE8" box="[1204,1374,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Ponomarenkoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was proposed (Olmi, 2010). Of course, the subfamily based on 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714B1A5508FC71FDCC" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="2010" box="[810,980,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Ponomarenkoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714B1A5508FC71FDCC" box="[810,980,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Ponomarenkoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had to be named 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFFFE714CAA5508FAC3FDCC" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="2010" box="[1178,1382,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="433" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponomarenkoinae">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFFFE714CAA5508FAC3FDCC" box="[1178,1382,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="433" pageNumber="434">Ponomarenkoinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
